.TH DtWsmOccupyAllWorkspaces 3X "" "" "" ""
.ds )H Hewlett-Packard Company
.ds ]W Common Desktop Environment 1.0: January 1994
.SH NAME
\fBDtWsmOccupyAllWorkspaces\fP \- put a window into all workspaces.
.iX "DtWsmOccupyAllWorkspaces"
.iX "workspace functions" "DtWsmOccupyAllWorkspaces"
.sp .5
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB
\&#include <Dt/Wsm.h>
.sp .5
void DtWsmOccupyAllWorkspaces (
.br
.ta 0.75i 2.20i
	Display *	\fIdisplay\fP,
.br
	Window	\fIwindow\fP)
.br
.sp .5
\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
This function is designed to work with the Common Desktop Environment
window/workspace manager (dtwm).
.PP
\fBDtWsmOccupyAllWorkspaces\fP puts a window into all currently defined
workspaces. The window will also be placed into new workspaces as they
are created.
.sp .5
.IP "\fIdisplay\fP" 1.00i
The X display.
.IP "\fIwindow\fP" 1.00i
The window to occupy all workspaces.
.PP
.sp .5
.SH RETURN VALUE
None.
.sp .5
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
\fBdtwm(1X)\fP, \fBDtWsmSetWorkspacesOccupied(3x)\fP.
.sp .5
